<br>
<br>
Welcome to the world of message board communities. People want something to talk about. When druidX or wizardZ reads a few threads from warriors (or anyone else) about how warrior taunt sucks, they do the message board equivalent of nodding their head wisely and agreeing. A few people making assertions loud enough can cause whole communities to go through a domino effect of agreement.<br>
<br>
Ask anyone who remembers the &quot;common knowledge&quot; of the day that stats such as STR, DEX, and AGI were the most important things for items to have. Anyone remember when the serpentine band was considered uber? That &quot;common knowledge&quot; started from the assertions of a few vocal people - I stress the word few - on whineplay, which then got parroted by many others, until it became accepted as gospel. <br>
<br>
When someone reads a post (hears a speech, etc.) from someone who seems to be intelligent and seems to have a valid new insight and/or just seems to pwnzor n00bs, it is a natural response for many people to agree vocally, thereby showing their own good judgement/intelligence/whatever for agreeing with this obviously intelligent/powerful person. It's called the bandwagon effect, and you will find it in any community. Look at current events for parallels.<br>
<br>
That's why I've said before that whining about an issue (by whining I mean exaggerating an effect or situation to bolster a position) is a self defeating exercise in a game like EQ where group desireability is all about perception. Do you want to know why there are often such large swings in class balance? Why rogues go from arguably the least balanced class in the game before Kunark to without a doubt the most powerful during late Kunark-early Velious? VI (SOE) can't just raise a class's abilities up to the point where they have parity, they have to raise their abilities up to the point where it is obvious to other players who might consider asking them to group. They have to break that ingrained perception created by the earlier imbalance.<br>
<br>
My wife still thinks rangers suck, because she hasn't really played with a ranger much since kunark. Ask rangers about reaping what you sew.<br>
<br>
EDIT: I just remembered a saying one of my Jesuit teachers used as one of the arguments for the existence of God: &quot;A million Frenchmen can't all be wrong.&quot;<br>
<br>
Yes they can. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=14686">Graal MacBladefury</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
