The mob comes in. The Tank engages. The slower slows or tashed and slows . The snarer snares .. ...<br>
<br>
Here is the point. At this point the Paladins and Sks are way way better in Gaining aggro and holding it for some seconds.<br>
At this point ... and most of you have written it ... At this point the warrior is loosing his aggro except he is lucky with a nice proc or some nice hits.<br>
<br>
Maybe we all as tanks would not notice that in a way .. .but all others hate it ... yeah they hate it beeing the target of the mob and beeing hit.<br>
<br>
