1. Paladin ... cast a fast stun ... chance for aggro is very very high maybe stun nr 2 .. chance is ultimate high for regainig aggro .. Time cost max 4 seconds.<br>
2. Sk some possibilities maybe not so good as the ones of the Palli but in around 4 to 6 seconds he should be able to 100 % regain aggro<br>
3. Warrior... hit taunt ... when no success ... wait for 6 seconds for another taunt making direktly after taunt a /shield ( 3 min refresh ) so the damage taken to the XX is maybe halved. After 6 seconds try another taunt ... ... .. <br>
<br>
So now we come to the harder part. The warrior will have to do this part more often than the Sk and the Palli cause they throw their high aggro spells out when mob is incomming. <br>
<br>
I always start a fight with a kick/disarm and try to start hitting at the same time so that I have hit kick disarm as a aggrostarter ... Then I wait for the message of landing spells and try to time Taunt if its nessessary ...<br>
<br>
