<br>
Warriors have always discussed these issues and our preveious &quot;gipe&quot; session was the &quot;state of warriors&quot; thread last July and it did not touch on the issues being argued in the community today.<br>
<br>
Warriors were unhappy with what they got or rather didn't get in SoL and PoP. What sparked the inferno that is this argument was that thread on the cleric message board. <br>
<br>
At that time, warriors weren't going around saying we weren't wanted or that we were sub-par tanks. We were griping about not being able to generate enough agro to keep the slower from dying right away. We were griping about the casters getting all the drops because all the drops were parchments.<br>
<br>
Warriors had issues before this, but as usuall, after an initial flare up over one thread that died a month later, we went back to discussing if breast plate a was better than b and does beg really generate agro.<br>
<br>
We did not start this particular argument. Infact, when the warriors vs knights argument first came about, many, including myself were quick to deny that knights had a significant advantage over warriors in exp group tanking. However, through a lot of parsing on this board, the paladin board and even the monk board, and through a lot of &quot;don't tank, we want the sk to tank today&quot; a lot of warriors fully opened their eyes to the condition they were relegated to by the community and by soe.<br>
<br>
So before anyone goes off and says that warriors are just b1thching again, read up on the history of why we are complaining. <br>
<br>
Agro is half of what makes a tank a tank. If you aren't getting hit you aren't tanking. Initial agro in  PoP is a serious problem since slowers and healers prefer to have someone who can ensure agro group with them. <br>
<br>
Yes there will always be exceptions to the rule, but this what slowers and healers have decided. <br>
<br>
<br>
I admire Frodlin and Glatius they have stood up for the warrior class from day one. Frodlin has produced much evidence from parsing and presented it to knights on the Paladins of Norrath board. Anyone who has contested his numbers, then done the parsin he has, has come up with similar numbers. <br>
<br>
If you want to contest Frodlin's numbers, or his calling your numbers BS, go parse. Otherwise you are a  BS'ing fool who will get no respect here.<br>
<br>
If you want to tell me that warriors are just fine today, you had better damn well provide the data to back it up. Annecdotal evidence is nice to have since it gives the perception of the situation. However, if you are going to pull numbers from that evidence, please hose the bull sh1t from those numbers first. <br>
<br>
Lastly, DO NOT TELL US WARRIORS TO GO GET SOME PIECE OF CRUTCH EQUIPMENT! That argument is the weakest of all. VI posted that the majority of toons were between level 46 and 55 across all servers (see the EQ Live-Fippy's Facts section). Until those pieces of equipment can be purchased by all for 50 pp each in the plane of knowledge or some other place, that argument is bunk. <br>
<br>
